													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/rudizygadlo/">Rudi Zygadlo</a></h6>
													Rudi Zygadlo is a writer and musician based in Glasgow. By day, he writes about culture and scores podcasts for <em>The Guardian</em>. By night, he releases music under various guises, including Lully. Rudi has been learning to drive for 17 years and loves table tennis. Instagram: @rudizyga; Twitter: @rudizygadlo																									</div>
